        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-03 16:55:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAre you testing with ovn-kubernetes addon. (https://github.com/onap/multicloud-k8s/blob/master/kud/deployment_infra/playbooks/configure-ovn-kubernetes.yml). Currently ovn-kubernetes addon is not supported and it is not part of the plan to support it. ovn4nfv is being used to provide multiple interfaces.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "655e060f6612c2841f6184343b01476f6a349f7d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5550,
          "name": "Konrad Banka",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kbanka.os@gmail.com",
          "username": "kbanka"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-04 09:33:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi,\nYes, this change was tested both with and without ovn-kubernetes addon installed (and worked in both scenarios).\nI was not aware of lack of support for ovn-kubernetes in multicloud-k8s' KUD, but, nevertheless, I think this fix could still stay, as it's flexible enough to work in both environments.\nDo you agree?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
